00083 /*
00084  * Name:   ammsgtypes
00085  *
00086  * Purpose: Contains an enumerated list of values that identify an
00087  *          AM packet's "type" field.
00088  *
00089  *          Packets with these type fields are sent/received over
00090  *          Inter-process communication channels
00091  *
00092  * Members: AMMINTYPE         -   Absolute minimum defined message type
00093  *          AMTYPEQMIREQUEST      QMI Request packet from an application
00094  *          AMTYPEQMIRESPONSE     QMI Response packet to an application
00095  *          AMTYPEQMINOTIFICATION QMI Notification packet
00096  *          AMMAXTYPE         -   Absolute maximum defined message type
00097  *          AMINVALID         -   Not a valid type. Used in some returns
00098  *
00099  * Note:    None
00100  *
00101  */
00102 enum ammsgtypes {
00103     /* Absolute minimum message value */
00104     AMMINTYPE = 0x0000,
00105     /* AMQMI Range: 0x00C0 to 0x00FF */
00106     AMTYPEQMIMIN = 0x00C0,
00107     AMTYPEQMIREQUEST = AMTYPEQMIMIN,
00108     AMTYPEQMIRESPONSE,
00109     AMTYPEQMINOTIFICATION,
00110     AMTYPEQMIMAX,
00111     /* AMSDK Range: 0x0100 to 0x01FF */
00112     AMTYPESDKMIN = 0x0100,
00113     AMTYPESDKREQUEST = AMTYPESDKMIN,
00114     AMTYPESDKRESPONSE,
00115     AMTYPESDKNOTIFICATION,
00116     AMTYPESDKMAX,
00117     /* Maximum currently defined message + 1 */
00118     AMMAXTYPE = AMTYPESDKMAX,
00119 
00120     /* Invalid message - Always last in this list */
00121     AMINVALID = 0xFFFF
00122 };

00133 /*
00134  * Name:    amqmirrparms
00135  *
00136  * Purpose: QMI Request Response parameter structure
00137  *
00138  * Members: amresultcode        - Used when building QMIRESPONSE to indicate
00139  *                                success or a timeout occurred.
00140  *
00141  *          amqmixactionlen     - QMI transaction length. This field is here in
00142  *                                case we need to support multiple QMI service
00143  *                                requests in a single transaction. For a single
00144  *                                QMI service request in a transaction, this field
00145  *                                should be equal to the QMI message length.
00146  *
00147  *          amqmireqtimeout     - Application-specified timeout waiting for a responsea
00148  *
00149  *          amqmisvctype        - QMI Service type
00150  *
00151  * Note:    The size of the fields in this structure are coded to match the
00152  *          definition of the Generalized QMI transaction structure as per
00153  *          80-VB816-1_A_QMI_Architecture.pdf
00154  */
00155 struct amqmirrparms {
00156     enum eQCWWANError   amresultcode;
00157     swi_uint32          amqmixactionlen;
00158 
00159     /* QMUX SDU preamble fields */
00160     swi_uint32          amqmireqtimeout;
00161     swi_uint8           amqmisvctype;
00162 };

00164 /*
00165  * Name:    amsdkrrparms
00166  *
00167  * Purpose: SDK Request Response parameter structure
00168  *
00169  * Members: amsdkxactionlen   - SDK transaction length.
00170  *          amsdkreqtimeout   - Application-specified timeout waiting for a response
00171  *          amsdkrrtype       - SDK req/resp type
00172  *          amsdkparms        - Parameters for the req/resp, one of the following:
